.TH simple_shell 1 "November 2025" "Holberton School" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a simple UNIX command interpreter
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B simple_shell
program is a simple command interpreter that mimics the behavior of the UNIX shell.
It reads commands from standard input and executes them.

.SH FEATURES
.TP
\fB•\fR Displays a prompt and waits for user input.
.TP
\fB•\fR Executes commands with arguments.
.TP
\fB•\fR Handles the PATH to locate executables.
.TP
\fB•\fR Supports built-in commands like \fBexit\fR and \fBenv\fR.
.TP
\fB•\fR Works in both interactive and non-interactive modes.

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.EX
$ ./hsh
($) /bin/ls
hsh main.c shell.c
($) exit
$
.EE

Non-interactive mode:
.EX
$ echo "/bin/ls" | ./hsh
hsh main.c shell.c
$
.EE

.SH AUTHORS
See the AUTHORS file for a list of contributors.
